## Enhancement
cannot detect the file system handle that was  mount on a block device using the block device handle 

as previously talked to @geky we need a a way to get the file system handle from the block device, 
we are using multiple partitions (means multiple mbr block devices) and multiple file system.
we need a way to get from the MBR the file system that was mounted on him (and then the mount point) 

something like that:
```
TFileSystem fs[2];
MBRBlockDevice part[2];
int count = 0;
for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
    part[count] = MBRBlockDevice(i);
    int err = part.init();
    if (!err) {
        printf("partition %d exists\n, i);
        fs = part[count].getFileSystemHandle;
        printf("mount point of parition %d is %s\r\n",i,fs.getMountPoint());
        count++;
    }  
}
```

**Suggested enhancement**
add and api to get the file system handle

